text: I’m going to put forth a couple names that I have HUNCHES in so far as other celebrities who may have “faked” their “deaths.”  What’s a Hunch?  It’s a feeling or guess based on intuition rather than known facts.  I haven’t had time to look into who else is “behind the curtain,” but these other names have come into my awareness.  Could Jim Morrison, Janis Joplin or John Lennon be some of the others waiting to “reappear?”  Go ahead and make your own guesses.  However, never lose sight of the fact that these individuals feared for their life and also the lives of their families and friends.  What kind of evil could be so great that they would walkway from everything:  loved ones, immense talents, fame & adoration, wealth.  The question of “what kind of evil” is the central theme here.  Let’s reassure them, whoever they are, that it’s safe to come out of the shadows.
author: Annette Hein

text:
Take Action Now!  Princess Diana, John F. Kennedy, Jr., Carolyn Bessette Kennedy, and Lauren Bessette are ALIVE.  There’s also a long list of celebrities, entrepreneurs and others including David Bowie, Elvis, Marilyn Monroe, Michael Jackson, Robin Williams, Steve Jobs, and Whitney Houston who are alive, too.  There are many more whose names are not listed.  Over time, each one of them joined International Witness Protection Programs for protection.  
Yes, they went into hiding to protect the lives of loved ones and themselves from unimaginable evil.  Now, they’re ready to come out and share their stories with the world.  However, you can imagine that they want to do so in the best way possible considering that they had to leave their families, friends, and careers behind.  This is where WE COME IN.  I’m urging you to share this news with family, friends and in every forum possible (for example, fan websites, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, wherever you can).  Post messages of Greetings and Love to any of the people on the list.  Let’s show them that we are anxious to see them again and are willing to respectfully allow each one of them the opportunity to tell their own stories.  
As you can imagine, this is a really BIG DEAL for all of these folks.  Let’s give them lots of LOVE, RESPECT and ENCOUREMENT and ask them to please come forward now.  Use a free online translation program if you cannot read this message.
author: Annette Hein

text: Woke up this morning and remembered her. Never read her bio before, so I did a Wikipedia search and saw her as the second greatest singer of all time. Had to research the first, listened carefully to several of their best songs, and was REALLY shocked. No disrespect to other singers but Whitney Houston is BY MILES THE UNDISPUTED GREATEST SINGER OF ALL TIMES. The comparison is more of a joke, a kind of respect others do deserve but in placing Whitney as second behind that voice, it's a kind of big disrespect to me. Whitney is WAYYYY SUPERIOR in every way and the records, even number of views on here are just an indication of which voice truly compelled and touched people with its once in a lifetime beauty! What an absolute darling...there will never be another of you. RIP.

text: I’m going to put forth a couple names that I have HUNCHES in so far as other celebrities who may have “faked” their “deaths.”  What’s a Hunch?  It’s a feeling or guess based on intuition rather than known facts.  I haven’t had time to look into who else is “behind the curtain,” but these other names have come into my awareness.  Could Jim Morrison, Janis Joplin or John Lennon be some of the others waiting to “reappear?”  Go ahead and make your own guesses.  However, never lose sight of the fact that these individuals feared for their life and also the lives of their families and friends.  What kind of evil could be so great that they would walkway from everything:  loved ones, immense talents, fame & adoration, wealth.  The question of “what kind of evil” is the central theme here.  Let’s reassure them, whoever they are, that it’s safe to come out of the shadows.
author: Annette Hein

text: My miniature schnauzer passed in 2017. My grandfather has this thing where he makes these “movies” which are collections of videos of different things we experience. He made one when my dog passed away, filled with all the memories of my dog’s 13 year long life. He played this song over it, and it still makes me cry to this day. Casey, if you’re out there, staring down at me… hanging out with the souls of other beautiful pets, I just wanted to say I miss you. I love you more than anything in the world.

text:
I dedicate this song to my father on behalf of my mother who made it to their 50th wedding anniversary January 1, 2023 to die just 21 days later. Our hearts are in a million pieces but their love… will never be broken and will live forever in my mother, me - his daughter and grandchildren. 

Thank you Apa (a nickname I had for my dad), I miss you more then words can say 😢. I’m happy you were ready to go and I did everything I could for you. What was left to say was how proud I was of you and how proud I was/am to be your daughter. I’m so sorry I didn’t tell you when you where here physically on this earth. 

For those wondering my dad went into full kidney failure and didn’t want dialysis but wanted to make it to their 50th wedding anniversary so he changed his plans and went against his own wishes and decided to have a dialysis port put in. When they surgically went in there and made the first cut, they found a tumor and realized he had lymphoma which had spread upon opening the incision more and the diagnosis of terminal cancer was made (in late 2022). He didn’t suffer until the last few days of his life as he was a religious man and knew God had a plan for him. He told me he was ready to go home (heaven). My dad was at peace and so were we but, it doesn’t take away from the fact we miss him and continue to love him each and everyday!

text: This is, and will always be, an epic song that defined Houston and that time period.  It's also one I can practically never listen to.  I felt that way about someone once; as a naïve and withdrawn college student the lecturer for one of my classes called me on a Saturday morning asking me if I could fix her car.  I barely knew her and she'd gotten my number from the student directory.  It was just a loose wire for the starter motor, she was overjoyed it was no problem and bought me lunch and told me every detail of her life.  It was a setup to meet me outside of class, although she later denied it--she wasn't devious enough to disable her car but was taking advantage of the situation.  I thought an unlikely once in a lifetime May-December romance had begun.  A few years before she had nearly died in the hospital and also had found out her husband was cheating with her best friend, and now for some reason she'd chosen me while trying to finish her PhD and restart her life.  It ended after four years with me finally seeing she was a trashy alcoholic stringing along her estranged husband who paid the bills, a late twenties age boyfriend, and several younger men my age.  She'd disappear for days at a time doing who knows what, and had enormous legal and financial problems.  At the worst after her third DUI she was going to flee the country rather than face 30 days in jail, on top of her $800 a month in parking tickets and finally losing the family home over back taxes.  This song came out near the end of that, when I still kept thinking she was a good person just facing unreal problems, and vainly hoping if I told her I loved her enough it would fix everything.  I should have let go and walked away after the first few months, and every time this song comes up I remember being in that no-win situation.
author: Red Tiger

text:
Whitney Houston, too❓
Can’t be true, can it❓ What a Star-Studded list 🌟🤩! 

Did Whitney, Elvis, Robin Williams, Marylin Monroe, David Bowie, and Steve Jobs enter into the same Witness Protection Program as Michael Jackson? Now’s the time to start believing that anything is possible. Also, be “open” to the idea that perhaps the world you’ve been living in was not quite what it seemed.

No matter what, this is the time for each person to ponder this question. What would I do if confronted with demonic evil unlike anything the average man has ever seen? If offered enough “stuff,” would I step into it or walk away? What would you do?

BTW: Who else do you think would have a need to go into the same Witness Protection Program? Here’s a guess: Princess Diana. You know, there are others…wait and see!  

Are you starting to get the feeling that this story may be but a small part of the greatest story on Earth? 🌍💚
author: Annette Hein

text: Oh, G. Extraña fue la historia. Pareciera que fue un absurdo... pero no, no lo fue. A veces hay que vivir situaciones que nos llevan al límite para que nos sacudan por completo. El mundo que conocí, cambió por completo. Y tú estuviste como una presencia etérea que me dio cobijo. Ahora, sé que nada o poco significó para ti, pero para mí, no imaginas. Incluso así, sólo  puedo asegurar que siempre te amaré de una forma que no hay palabra para describirlo. Si no puedo alcanzarte, créeme que en el espacio donde o existe separación, donde somos las cualidades de Dios, ahí, tu y yo, somos. Dicha eterna, G, dicha siempre.

text:
Whitney Houston, too?
Can’t be true, can it?
Did Whitney, Elvis, Robin Williams, Marylin Monroe, David Bowie, and Steve Jobs enter into the same Witness Protection Program as Michael Jackson? Now’s the time to start believing that anything is possible. Also, be “open” to the idea that perhaps the world you’ve been living in was not quite what it seemed.

No matter what, this is the time for each person to ponder this question. What would I do if confronted with demonic evil unlike anything the average man has ever seen? If offered enough “stuff,” would I step into it or walk away? What would you do?

BTW: Who else do you think would have a need to go into the same Witness Protection Program? Here’s a guess: Princess Diana. You know, there are others…wait and see!  

Are you starting to get the feeling that this story may be but a small part of the greatest story on Earth?

text:
Whitney Houston, too?
Can’t be true, can it?
Did Whitney, Elvis, Robin Williams, Marylin Monroe, David Bowie and Steve Jobs enter into the same Witness Protection Program as Michael Jackson? Now’s the time to start believing that anything is possible. Also, be “open” to the idea that perhaps the world you’ve been living in was not quite what it seemed.

No matter what, this is the time for each person to ponder this question. What would I do if confronted with demonic evil unlike anything the average man has ever seen? If offered enough “stuff,” would I step into it or walk away? What would you do?

BTW: Who else do you think would have a need to go into the same Witness Protection Program? Here’s a guess: Princess Diana. You know, there are others…wait and see!  

Are you starting to get the feeling that this story may be but a small part of the greatest story on Earth?
author: Annette Hein

text:
This is the problem with my generation, we were fed an exceptionally beautiful and moving diet of lies that told us that to love someone you must leave them when things get tough instead of staying the course and living out the enduring and everlasting love that our hearts were screaming for!  When it ceases being sweet and tender at all times just move on while pining away for a love you are unwilling to participate in (give what you so desperately want to receive), all while foolishly making ourselves think that our love for the other (or theirs for us) is too great to live out together!  Lame!  And thank you Jesus for waking me up to that!

In Christ,
Andrew
author: Andrew

text:
THIS GOES ON TO GOSHERS:
Young people need to go to  their grandparents and get down the history of Ghana before carrying on cameras to vlog and comment about historical events with a whole lot of misinformations.
UGCC did not advocate for independence of the Gold Coast in the shortest time, they as  the bousurezees did not want to get the colonialist British - their slave masters - mad. They did not want to fight, and had remained as calm as a lamb so that the British could "trust" them and hand over power to them only on the terms of the demonic British.
 UGCC members even went to see that queen in England and asked her to delay the transfer of power and the independence and were expressing that the Gold Coast was not "matured" to be on her own. Yes they did all that.
It was Kwame Nkrumah who brought down the fire to the British  feet and forced them for "independence now" !!

The history on the damaged bronze statue of Kwame Nkrumah should be a history every child should know but Ghana being what she is  where our leaders are ready to erase our past for money as seen in our  new elementary history book, historical events like this that had implicated many prominent politicians of today will remain foggy. And that's where your grandpas and grandmothers come in to fill in the blank spots.

When the CIA, UK and the Israeli sponsored overthrow instigated by UGCC members of the present president's family including JB Danquah was carried on successfully, the masses of Ghanaians were lied to that Kwame Nkrumah was an "evil" man so the anger of the people and the young military men got into their head and supported by the coup makers pulled down his  original bronze statue and  deliberately damaged it to what it is today.

Today, pan-Africanism, integration and industrialization became the clarion call at every conference and  the name Kwame Nkrumah is being mentioned and how he had warned us of the dangers that we are suffering of today would caught up with us if we did not heed to the call he made in 1963 to unite or suffer poverty.

The make-over of this memorial is in fact carried out with a great reluctance on the part of the state simply because the whole Africa is now INVOKING on Kwame Nkrumah's name from Dr. Arikana to Malema, PLO Lumumba to President Museveni, Paul Kagame , President Ruto and  African America / Caribbean diasporians, and  many others including the guest of honor to the recent Ghana's independence celebration - the ECOWAS chairman the president of Guinea Bissau.
Why the reluctance? Because some people want to replace and erase the importance of Kwame Nkrumah and what he stood for with a very unknown figure such as JB but the air blowing now across Africa won't allow it no matter how hard they try it.
Kwame Nkrumah never die.
author: Borderless Africa
